        {
          "id": 68521,
          "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Benzoyl acetate</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 68522,
          "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Benzoyl lactate</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 68523,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Benzoyl glycine</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">In a biochemistry quiz focusing on metabolic pathways and their end products, a question is posed regarding the nature of hippuric acid, a compound involved in the detoxification processes in the body. The participants are asked to identify the correct composition of hippuric acid from the options provided. Which of the following best describes the chemical structure of hippuric acid?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8572326",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 30074,
      "difficulty_level": "difficult",
      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. D) Benzoyl glycine</span></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Hippuric acid</strong> is formed from the conjugation of <strong>benzoic acid with glycine </strong>in the<strong> liver, </strong>resulting in its <strong>excretion in the urine</strong>. This process is part of the body&#39;s mechanism for <strong>detoxifying certain substances</strong>, including some <strong>environmental toxins</strong> and <strong>dietary</strong> <strong>components.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A. Benzoyl glutamine:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> This option<strong> incorrectly </strong>pairs<strong> benzoic acid with glutamine</strong>; the <strong>correct</strong> amino acid involved in the formation of <strong>hippuric acid is glycine.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B. Benzoyl acetate:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> While <strong>acetate </strong>is a common <strong>metabolic intermediate,</strong> it is<strong> not</strong> involved in the formation of<strong> hippuric acid.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D. Benzoyl lactate:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> <strong>Lactate</strong> is involved in <strong>anaerobic metabolism </strong>but is <strong>not conjugated</strong> with <strong>benzoic acid to form hippuric acid.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">PHASE TWO REACTIONS &ndash; CONJUGATIONS</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Benzoic acid&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">is conjugated with <strong>glycine</strong> to form <strong>hippuric acid (benzoyl glycine) </strong>(excreted in urine)</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Glycine + Benzoyl CoA &rarr; Benzoyl glycine (hippuric acid) + CoA</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">As the <strong>conjugation</strong> occurs in <strong>liver</strong>, it is an index of <strong>liver function. </strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: DM Vasudevan 9/e: p 480,481.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
